        -:  139:     *
        -:  140:     * If it is not possible to add the SEXP constructor, e.g you don't control
        -:  141:     * the type, you can specialize the as template to perform the
        -:  142:     * requested conversion
        -:  143:     *
        -:  144:     * This is used for example in Environment, so that for example the code
        -:  145:     * below will work as long as there is a way to as<> the Foo type
        -:  146:     *
        -:  147:     * Environment x = ... ; // some environment
        -:  148:     * Foo y = x["bla"] ;    // if as<Foo> makes sense then this works !!
        -:  149:     */
